  "text": "The Kubernetes controller work queue with rate limiting is implemented in the client-go library and used throughout the Kubernetes controller manager. The core implementation resides in staging/src/k8s.io/client-go/util/workqueue/:\n\n**Queue Interfaces and Implementations:**\n\n1. **Basic Queue (queue.go)**: The TypedInterface and Typed struct define the fundamental queue operations (Add, Get, Done). TypedInterface specifies the contract with methods for adding items, getting the next item to process, and marking items as done.\n\n2. **Rate Limiting Queue (rate_limiting_queue.go)**: TypedRateLimitingInterface extends TypedDelayingInterface with rate-limited re-enqueueing capabilities through AddRateLimited, Forget, and NumRequeues methods. RateLimitingInterface is the deprecated non-generic variant.\n\n3. **Rate Limiters (default_rate_limiters.go)**: Two main implementations are provided:\n   - **ItemExponentialFailureRateLimiter** (TypedItemExponentialFailureRateLimiter): Implements exponential backoff with baseDelay*2^(num-failures) logic, configurable with maximum delay constraints. When and NumRequeues methods track failures per item, while Forget clears tracking for successful items.\n   - **BucketRateLimiter** (TypedBucketRateLimiter): Adapts golang.org/x/time/rate's token bucket limiter to the workqueue API, providing overall rate limiting across all items.\n\n4. **Delaying Queue (delaying_queue.go)**: TypedDelayingInterface extends TypedInterface with AddAfter method to support delayed re-enqueueing, which is essential for the rate limiting mechanism.\n\n**Reconcile Loop Pattern:**\n\nControllers implement the standard reconcile loop using the queue operations:\n\n1. **staging/src/k8s.io/client-go/examples/workqueue/main.go**: Provides a canonical example with Controller.processNextItem demonstrating the pattern: queue.Get() to retrieve work, queue.Done() to mark completion, and queue.AddRateLimited() for retries with rate limiting. Error handling calls queue.Forget() on success or when max retries exceeded.\n\n2. **pkg/controller/deployment/deployment_controller.go**: DeploymentController uses TypedRateLimitingInterface in processNextWorkItem (lines 488-492) which implements the core pattern: queue.Get() blocks until work is available, deferred queue.Done() ensures cleanup, queue.AddRateLimited() requeues on error with exponential backoff.\n\n3. **pkg/controller/bootstrap/tokencleaner.go**: TokenCleaner controller demonstrates the pattern in processNextWorkItem (lines 146-150) where queue.Get() retrieves the next token secret to clean, queue.Done() marks processing completion, and queue.AddRateLimited() retries failed cleanups.\n\n4. **pkg/controller/bootstrap/bootstrapsigner.go**: BootstrapSigner uses the queue in its syncLoop with queue.Get() and queue.Done() pattern for processing bootstrap CSR signing requests.\n\nThe design ensures fair work distribution, prevents thundering herd, and implements exponential backoff for failing operations, making it suitable for production Kubernetes deployments handling thousands of objects."
}
